I made this with @fuseodg and @killbeatzgh in 2016 when I was travelling in Ghana. Fuse has me stay at his house out there and we would made 3 or 4 songs a day, then he’d invite 200 or so people round in the evening and we’d party to the songs we made. It was such a fantastic atmosphere and vibe, each day was different and felt like we were creating the next party. This song was created after a wild night and is just about a hangover but I love it. Shout to @dannocean too. Check out Lazy Day now x

New music out today. I made this song with @losangelesconfidential back in 2013. Me and him must’ve made 11 or 12 songs over the course of a few weeks whilst in LA, Some with @rudimentaluk, some by ourselves. I remember going down late one night to his studio, about 4am and we sat and talked about everything in life. I pulled out a guitar and played some chords and sang a @bignarstie hook over it, Game instantly got in the booth, and 15 minutes later this song was created. I’m so happy it’s finally out. I’m such a huge fan of Game, and this album is brilliant. Please check it out. Shout out @bignarstie too. Born 2 rap out now ! (Also on the intro, check that out too) x
Found an old digital recorder with the first ever demo of You Need Me from 2007 today, weird hearing it back but cool at the same time. Thought I’d share, back to hibernation see ya xx
